President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of Nebraska due to severe storms, ice jams, and flooding that occurred from March 6 to April 3, 2010. This declaration allows federal aid to supplement state and local recovery efforts. Federal funding will be available to help with emergency work, as well as the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. The affected counties include Antelope, Arthur, Boone, Boyd, Butler, Cass, Colfax, Cuming, Dakota, Gage, Greeley, Hayes, Holt, Howard, Jefferson, Johnson, Lancaster, Loup, Madison, Nance, Nemaha, Nuckolls, Otoe, Pawnee, Pierce, Platte, Polk, Richardson, Saline, Seward, Stanton, Thurston, Valley, Wheeler, and York. Hazard mitigation measures will also receive federal funding on a cost-sharing basis statewide. Stephen R. Thompson has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. Additional designations may be made if requested by the state and deemed necessary based on further damage assessments.